video_description: Raspberry Palmiers üíñ Just 3 ingredients, so easy to make and the perfect heart-shaped cookie for Valentine‚Äôs Day!  Full recipe is on our website (link in bio) or BOOKMARK the recipe below üëá  RASPBERRY PALMIERS (makes 2 dozen) 14 oz puff pastry, thawed  1/2 oz freeze dried raspberries (linked on our amazon page) 1/2 cup granulated sugar, divided Optional: 2 oz white chocolate + more freeze dried raspberries for garnish Add the raspberries to a food processor and pulse into a fine powder.  Add ‚Öî of the sugar to a bowl, then sift the raspberry powder into the sugar and discard the seeds. Whisk until well combined. Place puff pastry on a clean surface, then sprinkle with remaining ‚Öì cup of (plain) sugar. Lightly roll out the rectangle with a rolling pin. Flip over the puff pastry, then sprinkle liberally with raspberry sugar. (NOTE: you may have sugar leftover. Just use enough to fully coat the puff pastry in an even layer.) Press it in with your hands, then use a rolling pin to roll it out. Most store bought puff pastry will be about 10x11 inches, but ours was a bit bigger, so we rolled it to about 13x14 inches. Fold the longer section of your puff pastry in half to mark the middle point. Then fold each end a little less than halfway to the middle and sprinkle with more raspberry sugar. Make another fold, folding each end towards the middle. Sprinkle on a little more regular sugar. Fold again so the two sides meet and press down gently with a rolling pin. Place in the freezer for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 400ÀöF. Remove from freezer and cut into ¬Ω-inch thick slices. Space about 2 inches apart on parchment paper and bake for 8-10 minutes, then flip with a spatula and cook for another 4-5 minutes, until golden brown and crispy. video_description: This can happen to anyone, please be careful! (I‚Äôve made so many videos about this, but of course, the one that blew up is the one with the least context, I explained in the comments when i first posted but I didn‚Äôt realise I could change my caption after so heres more details) I‚Äôm so incredibly grateful to be in a position today, where I can pay my bills without struggling, but my energy provider threw a random debt of over ¬£3K onto my monthly payment last month, upping my direct debit X 3, I live in a small flat on my own, my current usage doesn‚Äôt reflect this bill, but my supplier said if I don‚Äôt pay it, it could affect my credit. I refused to pay without investigation and put all payments on hold to prevent that. I‚Äôm stressed and scared but like I said I‚Äôm incredibly fortunate in my position, this was a choice for me. Most people can‚Äôt turn off the heating to avoid overcharges, the vulnerable, parents with children, elderly etc, they still have to pay these insane prices, and the debts on top by these predatory corporations. It happens ALL TOO OFTEN, It‚Äôs disgusting and isn‚Äôt talked about enough. It can happen to anyone! Netizens have been so helpful in my comments sharing what they did in my situation, offering guidance to others as well. Circle skirts and deep curves are notorious for their hemming difficulty as the length of the curve varies across the hem, therefore you often end up with tucks and pleats across the hemline. Here‚Äôs a step by step guide on how to hem curves. 1. Sew a basting stitch around 1cm from the edge of your curve. A basting stitch is a long length stitch with no back stitching.   2. Double fold that fabric, using the basting stitch as a guide, and pin the fabric down. 3. Pull the basting stitch, either from the top or side, here you‚Äôre easing the fabric in, kind of like gathering, but more subtle. 4. Sew your hem, and give it an iron. Ironing is key to making your hem look flat and smooth! 5. Unpick the basting stitch, and voila!            #teaganjacobs #sewingtutorial #sewingtips #sewinghack #sewtok #beginnersewing

Reduce heat to medium-low (make sure broth is no longer boiling). Do not stir. Pour in half of the eggs in a very slow and small stream. Carefully stir 1-2 times then pour in the other half and stir 1-2 times to create egg ribbons. Leave it alone. 6. Turn the heat to high. Bring to a boil and immediately turn off the heat.  7. video_description: Egg drop soup‚Äôs sexy cousin  1 1/2 cups frozen sweet corn 1 cup thinly sliced chicken breast (I used two thin sliced breasts) 1 tsp cornstarch  1 tsp oyster sauce  32oz carton of chicken or bone broth (4 cups) 1 Tbsp soy sauce 1/2 tsp garlic powder 1/2 tsp turmeric  1/2 tsp chicken bouillon powder 1 tsp white pepper Cornstarch slurry (3 Tbsp cornstarch + 4 Tbsp water)  3 eggs mixed w/ 1 Tbsp water 1 tsp sesame oil Give your corn a rough chop and thinly slice your chicken breast. Season chicken with cornstarch and oyster sauce. Bring your chicken/bone broth to a boil and add in your soy sauce and seasonings. Pour in your cornstarch slurry as you stir and wait for the broth to thicken just a bit. Once thickened, add in chicken and cook for a minute. Add in corn and prepare your egg mixture. Turn the heat down and make sure your broth is not bubbling to avoid your soup from getting cloudy. Slowly pour in your egg mixture as you stir to create long egg ribbons. Cut the heat and add in sesame oil. Garnish with lots of green onion razzle dazzle and enjoy!

video_description: Replying to @Sani0x Soft Sandwich Rolls  Detailed step-by-step written recipe is linked in my bio - click on the ‚Äúall bread + dough‚Äù recipes button.    Measurements: 390-420ml warm water 1 teaspoon honey, sugar or agave 1 Tablespoon (15ml) extra virgin olive oil 1.5 teaspoons (6g) instant yeast 500g white bread flour* 2 teaspoons (10g) fine sea salt  Once rolls are shaped, let them rest (covered at room temp) for about 45 minutes before baking.  Oven temp 230C/445F and place a vessel with water at bottom of oven to create steam in oven as it preheats. I just use a 9x5 loaf tin for this.  Bake for 10 minutes with steam in, remove the water and continue baking for another 6-8 minutes or until the bread is golden brown. I bake on the lowest rack as I find it browns the bottom of the bread better.  *500g is roughly 3.8-4 cups of flour. The flour should be fluffed up, spooned into cup and levelled to ensure it‚Äôs as accurately measured as possible. Scales are always best! Use the tutorial as a guide for consistency of dough and adjust water/flour slightly if needed Top tips: üçû The first time you make this bread, I suggest reducing the water in the recipe to 390ml when you initially mix the dough and then slowly add in the remaining 30ml if you feel the dough needs it to reach a similar consistency to my dough in the tutorial. video_description: The video is long, here's the list written out. Let me know if y'all want more recommendations. 1. Don't assume the roads will be drivable and the sidewalks walkable (if a truck is swerving, maybe your camry also isn't equipt) 2. Invest in ice cleats (amazon is cheaper than REI) 3. Get a pair of gloves, a beanie, and a headband (I like the North face etip gloves, costco merino wool, turtle fur headband, all under $20) 4. Get winter boots (Sorel + Pajar are great and Nordstrom rack + Marshals carries them) if you can, but fuzzy crocs also work 5. Keep your apartment at 78 (and ignore Oncur) 6. Get a fleece + waterproof dog jacket (I like ruffwear and only own one jacket per dog) 7. Stock up (don't hoard) on doggie bags 8. Pipes burst, be prepared to quickly seal off your apartment (duck tape + towels can work in a pinch) 9. Charge your battery packs (Living near a hospital doesn't mean you won't lose power) 10. $15 Budget Dollar Tree Date Night Appetizer, Dinner, & Dessert! Full Recipes and Price Breakdown: Appetizer: Pickle Fritters Dill pickles $1.25 Southern fry mix $1.25 Ranch for dipping $1.25 Appetizer Cost $3.75 Drain entire jar of pickles and chop finely.  Mix chopped pickles with dry fry mix until a tacky dough forms (for me this was about 1/4 to 1/3 of a cup of fry mix)  I pan fried these fritters in oil until cooked and then I drained on paper towels and I fried them a second time to get them ultra crispy.  Serve with ranch for dipping.   Main course: Creamy Gnocchi Skillet  Gnocchi $1.25 Sausage $1.25 Frozen Pepper stir fry $1.25 Cream cheese blend $1.25 Parmesan cheese $1.25 Mozzarella cheese $1.25 Main course cost $7.50 Bring a large pot of water up to a boil, cover and set aside.   In a skillet, fry and crumble the sausage until brown, do not drain.  The sausage fat will add extra flavor.  Add 2 handfuls (about half the bag) of pepper stir fry (mine was thawed) and sautee for a few minutes.  Stir in 6 oz of cream cheese blend cut into cubes and about 1/2 to 3/4 of a cup of the boiled water we had set aside earlier.  Continue to heat and stir until you have a smooth and creamy sauce and stir in 1/4 to 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese to taste.  Taste and season if desired.  Set aside. Return to your boiling water and cook your gnocchi for 3 to 5 minutes until it starts to float to the top.  Do not overcook this or it will be gummy.  As each gnocchi floats transfer them to your prepared cream sauce.  Gently stir the gnocchi and sauce together, top with mozzarella and broil until brown on top.  Desert: Cherry Cobbler  Muffin mix (mixed berry or blueberry) $1.25 Cherry pie filing $1.25 Vanilla ice cream $1.25 Desert cost $3.75 Mix muffin mix with 1/2 cup of water or milk.  Add cherry pie filling to the bottom of a baking dish and top with muffin batter.  Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes and serve warm with ice cream. #valentinesday #datenight #datenightideas #dollartreedinners #budgetdinners #budgetdatenight

video_description: Replying to @Fitzjitsu my healthy addiction #eggdropsoup #chinesetakeout  32oz carton of chicken or bone broth (4 cups) 1 Tbsp soy sauce 1/2 tsp garlic powder 1/2 tsp turmeric  1/2 tsp chicken bouillon powder 1 tsp white pepper Cornstarch slurry (3 Tbsp cornstarch + 4 Tbsp water)  3 eggs mixed w/ 1 Tbsp water 1 tsp sesame oil Bring your chicken/bone broth to a boil and add in your soy sauce and seasonings. video_description: Why he Can Never Shower With his Wife #cycle. On average, women tend to have a slightly higher body temperature than men, and this phenomenon is influenced by a combination of physiological and hormonal factors. Metabolic Rate: Women often have a slightly slower metabolic rate than men. A higher metabolic rate generates more heat, contributing to an elevated body temperature. Menstrual Cycle: Hormonal fluctuations during the menstrual cycle can impact body temperature. A slight rise in temperature is common after ovulation, potentially influencing the overall average. Thermoregulation: The female body's thermoregulation mechanisms, responsible for maintaining a stable internal temperature, may function with slight variations compared to males. Body Composition: Differences in body composition, such as higher body fat percentage in women, can contribute to insulation and heat retention, affecting overall temperature. video_description: This is why I insist that parents need support: they‚Äôre healing themselves, they‚Äôre healing their children, they often need to heal some parts of their marriage, and for many parents, they‚Äôre also supporting the physical + medical needs of THEIR OWN aging parents in the background! And ha, not to mention if they‚Äôre employed üôÉüôÉ This is why family therapy is so important. We MUST begin by supporting the parents so that they can lead the healing of their family.  In the family therapy that I have been extensively trained in and practice, Emotionally Focused Family Therapy, we divide therapy into two phases: 1) parental openness 2) child vulnerability. We do not bring the child and parent together until the parent is open to the child‚Äôs needs and vulnerability. This protects the child from getting hurt further and sets the parent up to successfully work with their child.  I decided to role play this particular dyad 1) bc I see it in around 1/3rd of mom-daughter dyads that I‚Äôve worked with 2) I also saw a good bit of this in the comment section of that viral post about parents taking accountability. More than one comment outright said, ‚Äúthey should validate me.‚Äù Lol.  My aim is not to attack mothers or fathers. It is to show where things go wrong and how that creates pain that then becomes a legacy of pain when we pass it down to our children. Family therapy involves examining our own relationships and experiences as children, identifying the pain that we have there, and working to heal both our own pain and that of our children‚Äôs. video_description: CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister interviews Gypsy Rose Blanchard, who was released from prison after serving eight years over a plot to kill her abusive mother, Dee Dee Blanchard. She pleaded guilty to second-degree murder in 2016 and admitted that she convinced her then-boyfriend to stab her mother to death. Blanchard was a victim of Munchausen syndrome by proxy, a rare disorder in which a caregiver feigns or exaggerates illness in someone to elicit attention or sympathy. She had spent her childhood and early adulthood believing she suffered from a host of serious ailments, including leukemia, muscular dystrophy and asthma. After the abuse she experienced at the hands of her mother came to light, Blanchard was sentenced to 10 years in prison and released two years early on December 28th. According to the Missouri Department of Corrections, she is expected to remain under parole supervision until June 2025. #cnn

video_description: How to fix skinny-fatüôÉ ‚ÄúSkinny-fat‚Äù is confusing? Because the more weight you try and lose, the worse the problem seems to get? That‚Äôs usually because people are trying to solve the wrong problemüí° The problem most people *think* they need to solve is having too much body fat. They try and solve this by: - adding endless cardio - and restricting food more and more But that‚Äôs only going to make the problem worse Because ‚Äúskinny-fat‚Äù doesn‚Äôt usually come from not having too much body fat, it comes from not having enough *muscle* underneath our fat to give us any shape or definition. To fix this, you would want to: - Focus on lifting heavy weights - Actually limit your cardio (probably not more than 1/3 of your total exercise) - And often times actually eat *more* food, not less It‚Äôs also important to note that every human body is different, so the exact solution for each person will be a little bit different - but this generally a good place to start ü§òüèº #skinnyfat #abs #coreworkout #cardio #fittok

video_description: Replying to @Fitzjitsu my healthy addiction #eggdropsoup #chinesetakeout  32oz carton of chicken or bone broth (4 cups) 1 Tbsp soy sauce 1/2 tsp garlic powder 1/2 tsp turmeric  1/2 tsp chicken bouillon powder 1 tsp white pepper Cornstarch slurry (3 Tbsp cornstarch + 4 Tbsp water)  3 eggs mixed w/ 1 Tbsp water 1 tsp sesame oil Bring your chicken/bone broth to a boil and add in your soy sauce and seasonings. video_description: #Ad Don‚Äôt spend all this time flipping individual small pancakes. Try this skillet pancake made with caramelized bananas! I made this skillet pancake using a serving of @lovemysilk Original Almondmilk, which is an excellent source of calcium and Vitamin E. As we head into the New Year, we‚Äôre all thinking about how we can feel better with our routines which is why I‚Äôm adding more Almondmilk into my mornings. Let‚Äôs all incorporate more Silk Almondmilk into our breakfast routines! Join the 7-day Silk Feel Planty Good Challenge during the month of January for a chance to win a lifetime of free breakfast on Silk. Stay tuned to learn how you can enter, in the meantime stock up on #SilkAlmondmilk #FeelPlantyGood See all Feel Planty Good Challenge details at challenge.silk.com. No purchase necessary. Void where prohibited. The Feel Planty Good Challenge is sponsored by Danone US, LLC. Open to legal residents of 50 U.S. & DC, 18 & older. Begins 12:00 a.m. ET on December 22, 2023 and ends 11:59 p.m. ET on January 31, 2024. For Official Rules, visit Challenge.silk.com. INGREDIENTS 1 cup all-purpose flour ¬º cup oats 2 teaspoons baking powder ¬º teaspoon baking soda ¬º teaspoon salt 1 large egg 1 cup Silk Original Almondmilk 2 tablespoons butter 1 banana, sliced in half vertically 2 tablespoons maple syrup INSTRUCTIONS 1. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In another larger bowl, whisk the egg until blended. Whisk in the Almondmilk, then fold in the dry mixture until well combined. Set aside. 2. When ready to cook, heat a large nonstick pan over medium heat. Melt the butter on the skillet. Add the two halved bananas, pour the maple syrup on top, and cook undisturbed for 2 minutes or until the edges of the banana start to brown. 3. Pour the entire pancake batter over the caramelized bananas and spread evenly to the edges of the pan. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and cook, shaking pan occasionally, until underside is golden brown and top is almost set, 7 to 8 minutes. 4. Use a rubber spatula to help slide the pancake onto a plate, then place the skillet over the plate and invert back into the skillet. Cook, uncovered, until the bottom is light golden and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 5 minutes more. Cut into 6 slices and enjoy immediately.

video_description: How my baby naps outside. You've probably seen all the viral tiktoks about Nordic babies napping outside alone and the benefits that come with it. My family and friends used to think I was crazy for letting my babies nap outside alone. It is very common in Denmark and the other Nordic countries to let your baby sleep outside alone. My oldest had his own pram at daycare for his outdoor naps. To let your baby nap outside, they have to be dressed properly. So let's break it down: First of all, avoid cotton since it absorbs moist, which gets cold very quickly. Think layers! Every baby is different, so you might have to adjust to your babies needs. Check frequently if your baby is too warm or not warm enough. The combination of clothing and sleeping bag is just one way to do it, some use a duvet, some use a snowsuit. Do whatever works for your baby and use whatever you have at hand. This is how I dress my baby: ‚Ä¢ thin wool layer ‚Ä¢ wool or fleece jumpsuit ‚Ä¢ double layered wool balaclava  ‚Ä¢ wool mittens and booties ‚ñ™Ô∏éinsulated pram ‚ñ™Ô∏émedical grade sheepskin ‚ñ™Ô∏éwind and waterproof down sleepingbag ‚ñ™Ô∏éextra blanket if necessary  ‚ñ™Ô∏épram cover ‚ñ™Ô∏é raincover when necessary  I know I know, wool is freaking expensive. I would know, I live in Denmark, everything I expensive üò© But check out Facebook marketplace or your local thriftstore for second hand wool for babies.  As someone who did not grow up with the tradition of letting babies sleep outside, it has definitely grown on me! Eventhough are spending winter in the Netherlands, we have brought our pram. Timothy Piazza (19) d!ed as the result of hazing at the Beta Theta Pi fraternity at Pennsylvania State University at University Park, Pennsylvania. On the night of February 2nd, 2017 while undergoing hazing activities for the fraternity, Timothy, on an essentially empty stomach, drank large amounts of alcohol in a short time as part of an obstacle course called "The Gauntlet", which required each pledge to drink from a bottle of vodka, drink a beer, and finally drink from a bag of wine. It later was revealed that Timothy took prescription anti-depressants, which contributed to his inebriation. The fraternity was supposed to be alcohol-free after a suspension in 2009. In this state of intoxication, he fell on the basement stairs of the house and was knocked unconscious. He was carried to a couch, where surveillance cameras captured a conspicuous bruise that bloomed on his left abdomen; however, this was shown to have originated from another one of the alcohol-fueled rush events for fraternities that Timothy had attended a week earlier. Jonah Neuman, Lars Kenyon, and Edward Gilmartin colluded in prohibiting witnesses from calling 9-1-1. Jonah threw someone against a wall, Edward labeled witnesses crazy and insane, whilst Lars downplayed the concerns of witnesses in group chats. Some time later, Timothy regained consciousness and rolled off the couch. Three brothers picked him up and placed him back on the couch. Security footage shows them poking Timothy in the face, to determine if he was okay, but he remained unconscious and unresponsive. At around 3:30 am on February 3rd, Timothy tried to get up, but once he reached a standing position, fell backward. He continued to stand up only to repeatedly fall back down. Once he was finally able to maintain balance, he staggered toward the lobby area of the house, but fell again headfirst into an iron railing and landed on a stone floor, likely incurring serious head trauma. He got up and tried to reach the front door but fell headfirst into it, knocking himself unconscious again. He later tried once more to ascend the basement stairs and was missing until several of the fraternity brothers discovered him several hours later behind the bar in the basement, cold and breathing rapidly. It was at this point that he was carried upstairs. After several minutes of debating on what the next step should be, the conclusion was made that Timothy‚Äôs injuries were indeed serious and that he would require medical attention. Before emergency assistance arrived, the brothers wiped bl00d from his face and attempted to dress him in an effort to warm him. At 10:48 am, emergency services arrived and Timothy was brought to Mount Nittany Medical Center, but was quickly transported to Penn State Milton S. Hershey Medical Center because of the severity of his injuries. Upon arrival, Timothy was rushed into surgery, where he was discovered to have a ruptured spleen and class IV hemorrhagic shock. His brain had swollen to the point that roughly half of his skull had to be removed to relieve the pressure. The surgeons attempting to save his life deemed the injuries to likely be nonrecoverable, and Timothy was pronounced d*ad in the early morning of February 4th, 2017. He was estimated to have had a bl00d alcohol content of nearly 0.40 on the night of the hazing incident. Timothy‚Äôs d*ath led to the largest criminal indictment against a fraternity and its members in American history. More than a dozen students were initially charged, some with involuntary m*nslaughter. Some of the most serious charges were dropped and others thrown out by judges. In March 2017, the Beta Theta Pi fraternity was permanently banned from Penn State.  In 2019, four members of the fraternity received sentences of one to nine months in jail and house arrest.  #truecrime #truecrimetiktok #timothypiazza

video_description: The Inner Work can help you understand, address, and heal any and all human issues you may find yourself struggling with. In the case of perfectionism, we have gone through traumatic experiences that imprinted our subconscious with an intimidation of wrongness and mistakes. Usually religion or harsh parenting where wrongness or mistakes are met with extreme rejection or punishment are a common source. Perfectionism is the mind trying to overcompensate for this paranoia by intimidating us to be perfect ‚Äúor else.‚Äù So even after the original intimidation is removed our subconscious continues the pressure because it still thinks it‚Äôs keeping us safe. In order to heal from this we need to actually allow ourselves to make peace with our humanness and realize we can only do the best we can in each moment with what we know at the time.  Mistakes and consequences that are uncomfortable are a natural part of life and are not personal. To make a mistake just means you have to go through the consequences of that choice and learn, but the mind of perfectionism makes us feel like it is life or death. This is a crippling pressure and internal stress overtime. Whoever originally passed this belief system onto us had not learned any grace in life themselves and most likely live in their own internal torture of impossible standards.  True self-confidence doesn‚Äôt come from being perfect all the time, it actually is the ability to recover from any setbacks with ease, grace, and most importantly optimism for the lessons learned. The irony is when we have this more relaxed confidence we tend to show up our best. Get The Inner Work to learn more about the healing journey and how to reach your full potential of a life of true freedom and lasting happiness. You can shape it in the air fryer since the mixture may be a bit soft and hard to form into logs beforehand. It will solidify while cooking!  4. Cook for 10 min at 410. 5. video_description: welcome back to my series where I‚Äôm turning a single $55 grocery list into your week of easy, healthy meals ‚Äî this is recipe #1! üíï if you‚Äôre new here, I post one recipe per day all week and all of them are gluten & dairy free and serve 3-4 people! the entire grocery list is in the caption of the previous video üòä  full recipe is below & also on my website!  ingredients: - 1/4 cup olive oil  - 3/4 large yellow onion, diced - 2-3 large carrots, diced  - 10oz sliced white mushrooms - 4 garlic cloves, minced - 1-2 tsp salt + more as needed - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1 tsp dried thyme - 2 tbsp cornstarch, arrowroot starch, or tapioca starch - 1/2 cup nutritional yeast - 3 + 1/4 cups vegetable broth - 1/2 cup water, plus more as needed - 2 tbsp coconut aminos or tamari - 1 cup wild rice, thoroughly rinsed - 1 heaping cup shredded kale - 1/2 15oz can full-fat coconut milk, shaken heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large pot, then add the diced onion and carrots. cook the onion and carrots, stirring periodically, for 10 minutes or until the onions are translucent, then add in the sliced mushrooms and minced garlic. stir and cook for another 10 minutes. mix in the salt, black pepper, and thyme and let the spices get aromatic, about 3-5 minutes. add in the starch and mix well to incorporate it into the vegetables. do the same with the nutritional yeast. pour in all of the vegetable broth, 1/2 cup of water, coconut aminos, and rinsed wild rice. put a lid on the pot and bring the soup to a boil. once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 40-55 minutes, stirring occasionally. once the rice is fully cooked, mix in the shredded kale and coconut milk.  allow the kale to wilt, then serve immediately or simmer over low heat until serving. store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to five days or in the freezer for up to a month. the final day of this week‚Äôs series where I turned a $55 grocery trip into 5 easy, healthy gluten-free & dairy-free dinners for this week üíï finishing off the week with a delish kale & chicken salad perfect for fall üçÇ  full recipe is below & also on my website!   maple rosemary chicken:  - 2 lb boneless chicken thighs - 2 tbsp + 1/3 cup olive oil - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp pepper - 1/2 tsp garlic powder  - 2 tbsp maple syrup - 1 tsp dried rosemary - 1 tsp dried thyme maple vinaigrette:  - 1/2 cup olive oil - 1/4 cup coconut aminos - 2 tbsp maple syrup - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1/2 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary - 1/2 tsp garlic powder kale salad:  - 4-6 heaping cups shredded kale - 1 + 1/2 - 2 cups butternut squash, cubed + seeds reserved (optional) & olive oil, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder for baking - 2-4 carrots, finely chopped - 8-10 dates, pitted and finely chopped - 2 tbsp fresh chopped rosemary or 2 tsp dried rosemary - 1 cup dry wild rice, cooked according to package instructions preheat oven to 375 & line a large & small sheet pan with parchment. add the squash/oil/salt/pepper/garlic (and seeds if desired) to the small pan and the chicken, 2 tbsp oil/salt/pepper/garlic to the large. place both in the oven. whisk together remaining 1/3 cup of olive oil, maple syrup, rosemary, and thyme for the maple rosemary chicken thighs. after 25 mins, remove both pans. set squash aside. cover the chicken in the maple rosemary sauce and place back in the oven for 10 minutes to finish baking. mix all vinaigrette ingredients in a bowl or jar. massage into the kale using tongs or clean hands and let sit at least 10 mins. when the chicken is done (165 degrees) slice it up. assemble the salad by adding the squash and seeds, diced carrots, chopped dates, and rosemary to the kale. mix in the chicken. serve in large bowls with a scoop of cooked wild rice on top and enjoy!! this is my series where I‚Äôm turning a single $55 grocery list into 5 easy, healthy gluten-free & dairy-free dinners for this week ‚Äî each recipe serves 3-4 people & this is recipe #4! üíï today we‚Äôre making the easiest sheet pan tofu ever!! full recipe is below & also on my website!   crispy tofu & carrots: - 14oz firm tofu - 3-4 large carrots, sliced + salt, pepper, & garlic powder to season - 2 tbsp cornstarch, arrowroot starch, or tapioca starch - 1/4 cup olive oil - 1 tsp salt - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 cup dry wild rice, cooked according to package instructions - 3 green onions, sliced - 1 tbsp sesame seeds (optional) maple rosemary sauce:  - 1/3 cup coconut aminos or tamari - 1/4 cup maple syrup - 1/2 tsp black pepper - 1/2 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary preheat your oven to 350 degrees and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. press your tofu in your preferred way (I wrap it in paper towels, then place it on a plate and put a heavy pan or press on top) for 20-30 minutes to remove the moisture. slice the carrots, then cut the tofu into cubes once it's done being pressed. in a bowl, combine the cubed tofu, starch, salt, black pepper, and garlic powder. use clean hands to coat all of the tofu in the starch and spices. add the sliced carrots to the sheet pan and toss in the olive oil and additional salt, black pepper, and garlic powder. add the tofu to the pan and spread out the carrots and tofu evenly. bake for 20-25 minutes, until the tofu is browning and carrots are tender. while it bakes, whisk together all of the sauce ingredients in a small bowl. pour the sauce over the tofu and carrots and use a spatula to coat them in the sauce. place back in the oven for 10-20 minutes, until crisp and caramelizing. serve the tofu and carrots with the cooked wild rice, top with the sliced green onions and sesame seeds and enjoy. store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to five days. #budgetshopping #groceriesonabudget #groceryshopping #groceryshop #groceryhaul #mealprep #mealprepping #mealprepideas #grocerylist #mealsonabudget #healthyonabudget #easyhealthyrecipes #glutenfreerecipes #dairyfreerecipes #traderjoes #sheetpanmeals #tofurecipe #fallrecipes

I hope you enjoy!!  full recipe is below & also on my website!   ingredients:  - 1/4 cup olive oil - 1/4 large yellow onion, diced - 1 + 1/2 - 2 cups butternut squash, cubed - 1 lb ground pork - 1 tsp salt + more as needed to taste - 1/2 tsp black pepper + more as needed to taste - 3 garlic cloves, minced or 1 tsp garlic powder - 1 tsp dried thyme - 1/2 tsp dried rosemary - 1/4 tsp ground sage + 1/4 tsp ground sage - 1 heaping cup shredded kale - 3/4 cup vegetable broth - 1/2 15oz can full-fat coconut milk, shaken (note this is a thin sauce, if you want it super saucy I would recommend going for a whole can) - 1/2 cup nutritional yeast - 12oz gluten-free pasta of choice, cooked according to package instructions heat the oil over medium heat in a large skillet, then add the onion and butternut squash. cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, then add in the ground pork. break apart the pork with a spatula and let cook for another 10-15 minutes, until the pork is fully browned and the onion is translucent. meanwhile, fully cook your pasta. mix in the salt, pepper, garlic, thyme, rosemary, and 1/4 tsp of sage to the pork mixture and let the spices get aromatic, about 5 minutes. incorporate the shredded kale to the mix and let it wilt. remove the pork mixture from the skillet and set aside. in the same skillet, add the vegetable broth and coconut milk and bring to a simmer. stir in the remaining 1/4 tsp of sage and nutritional yeast, and season with additional salt and black pepper. reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes. add the pasta to the skillet and mix to cover all the pasta in sauce. add the pork mixture and stir to incorporate. store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to four days or in the freezer for up to a month. enjoy!! When I was diagnosed with Hashimoto‚Äôs, I was told that this was a condition that likely would not improve. I remember feeling really defeated because I finally had a *why* behind why I was experiencing certain symptoms, but being told it would probably never get better was really discouraging. I was experiencing stubborn weight gain (even though I was SO focused on healthy eating and consistent exercise), chronic fatigue, and was always bloated. I had to take control of my health and advocate for myself, requesting additional lab work for antibodies, hormone health and more. I had to do a ton of research on nutrition strategies that could help thyroid function and created a plan for myself that combined anti-inflammatory, hormone-supporting foods and nutrients. When I made the correct changes, I finally started to feel better- within *days* I was less bloated, within months I was losing weight and my thyroid function improved. I continue to monitor my thyroid antibodies and have since added back in dairy. These nutrition strategies were in combination with thyroid medication! Without nutrition changes and medication only, my TSH was 18, so the diet is definitely making a difference here. video_description: What is Hashimoto‚Äôs?  Hashimoto‚Äôs thyroiditis is an autoimmune condition that results when the immune system attacks the thyroid tissues. In this situation, the immune system mistakes thyroid cells for unfamiliar invaders and launches an inflammatory response directed to destroy pathogens.  Over time, this destruction results in progressive hypothyroidism, or low thyroid activity. Although thyroid antibodies are often untested in those exhibiting hypothyroid symptoms, researchers suspect approximately 90% of low thyroid sufferers have autoimmune thyroiditis, most of whom are women. This is an important statistic because effective treatment for autoimmunity is vastly different than the standard protocol for low thyroid. For the millions of people suffering from autoimmune-induced low thyroid that are being treated with thyroid replacement therapy, alone, a degenerative disease is manifesting under the surface that will eventually cause debilitating and far-reaching symptoms.  Although Hashimoto‚Äôs is widely agreed upon in conventional and functional medicine circles to be the number one cause of low thyroid, most patients are not thoroughly tested for this condition. Because low thyroid symptoms are easily mistaken for other conditions, this disease is often overlooked, and patients are either misdiagnosed or told that it is all in their head and to go home.  How serious is Hashimoto‚Äôs disease?  Thyroid function is complex and involves a relationship between the pituitary gland, hypothalamus, and thyroid glands. However, adrenal glands and other systems throughout the body play a role in a healthy thyroid. The best way to identify the root cause of your thyroid imbalance is with proper testing. The problem with conventional approaches to thyroid, is in large part, the lack of essential testing. Most practitioners only test biproducts of the pituitary and thyroid glands. However, that approach does not consider countless other indicators of a damaged thyroid hormone process.
